---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const lastUpdated = "July 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Fynite's privacy policy — what information we collect, how we use it, and the choices you have."
  canonical="/privacy"
  noindex={false}
>
  <section class="page-header page-container">
    <p class="eyebrow">Privacy Policy</p>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="page-lede">Last updated {lastUpdated}</p>
  </section>

  <section class="page-body article-container">
    <p>
      This policy explains what information Fynite collects when you visit
      fynite.in, how it's used, and the choices available to you.
    </p>

    <h2>Information we collect</h2>
    <p>
      Fynite is a static publication. We don't require an account to read
      our stories, and we don't collect personal information unless you
      choose to give it to us directly &mdash; for example, by emailing us
      through the contact page.
    </p>
    <p>
      Like most websites, our hosting and analytics providers may
      automatically log standard technical information, such as browser
      type, device type, approximate location, and pages visited, to help us
      understand how the site is used and to keep it secure.
    </p>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      We use only the cookies or local storage necessary for the site to
      function correctly. We do not use cookies to build advertising
      profiles.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-party links</h2>
    <p>
      Our stories may link to external sites, videos, or posts we reference
      or credit. We aren't responsible for the privacy practices of those
      third-party sites, so we encourage you to review their policies
      separately.
    </p>

    <h2>How we use information</h2>
    <p>
      Any information you send us directly, such as through email, is used
      only to respond to you, to fact-check or follow up on story tips, or
      to improve Fynite. We don't sell personal information.
    </p>

    <h2>Your choices</h2>
    <p>
      You can control cookies through your browser settings. If you've
      contacted us directly and want your information removed from our
      records, email us and we'll act on that request.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy as Fynite grows. Material changes will be
      reflected by updating the date at the top of this page.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about this policy can be sent to
      <a href="mailto: borseujjwal24@gmail.com">hello@fynite.in</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    padding-top: 48px;
    padding-bottom: 40px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .page-header .eyebrow {
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
  }

  .page-lede {
    margin-top: 14px;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .page-body {
    padding-top: 48px;
    padding-bottom: 80px;
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .page-body h2 {
    margin-top: 2em;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
  }

  .page-body h2:first-of-type {
    margin-top: 1.6em;
  }

  .page-body p {
    margin-top: 1em;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .page-body a {
    color: var(--color-brand);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .page-header {
      padding-top: 36px;
      padding-bottom: 32px;
    }

    .page-body {
      padding-top: 36px;
      padding-bottom: 56px;
    }
  }
</style>
